    "body": "This PR is a follow-up of #94.\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n- Fix `gemm_symmetric` kernel hang and incorrect triangular scheduling on SM120 (RTX 5090)\r\n- Add `benchmarks/benchmark_gemm_symmetric.py` comparing against cuBLAS\r\n\r\n### Problem\r\n\r\n`gemm_symmetric` was broken on SM120 with two compounding bugs:\r\n\r\n1. **Kernel deadlock with `cluster_M=2`**: The `TriangularTileScheduler` combined with SM120's warp-level MMA (ldmatrix) barriers causes a hang when `cluster_M > 1`. SM120 uses 8 independent warps for MMA (vs SM90's warp-group WGMMA), and the symmetric epilogue's `copy_postact` barrier synchronization deadlocks with multi-CTA clusters.\r\n\r\n2. **Wrong triangular indexing with non-square cluster tiles**: After falling back to `cluster_M=1`, the config `tile=(128,256), cluster=(1,1)` gives a non-square cluster tile (128x256). `TriangularTileScheduler` assumes square cluster tiles (`num_clusters_per_problem = cluster_m * (cluster_m + 1) // 2`), so it computed **all** tiles instead of only the upper triangle -- no speedup over a full GEMM.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\n\r\nOn SM120, use `tile_M=128, tile_N=128, cluster_M=1, cluster_N=1`:\r\n- Square 128x128 cluster tiles -> correct triangular scheduling\r\n- No multi-CTA clusters -> no deadlock\r\n\r\n### Benchmark results (RTX 5090, bfloat16)\r\n\r\n| Shape | quack | cuBLAS | Speedup |\r\n|-------|-------|--------|---------|\r\n| (2048, 2048) | 319 TFLOPS | 168 TFLOPS | **1.90x** |\r\n| (4096, 4096) | 356 TFLOPS | 216 TFLOPS | **1.65x** |\r\n| (8192, 8192) | 451 TFLOPS | 232 TFLOPS | **1.94x** |\r\n| (4, 4096, 4096) | 446 TFLOPS | 212 TFLOPS | **2.11x** |\r\n\r\nOutput is perfectly symmetric (`D - D.mT == 0`), close to theoretical 2x speedup from computing only the upper triangle.",
